135
00:10:15,728 --> 00:10:18,715
The measuring principle: 

136
00:10:18,715 --> 00:10:20,478
to be able to measure with the level, 

137
00:10:20,478 --> 00:10:24,053
it is necessary that the line of sight
is horizontal. 

138
00:10:24,053 --> 00:10:30,699
We remind you here that the spirit level
used to calibrate the level, 

139
00:10:30,699 --> 00:10:35,707
we have here the guideline; 

140
00:10:35,707 --> 00:10:41,704
once the bubble is in the upper portion 
of the tube, 

141
00:10:41,704 --> 00:10:48,912
the tangent in this upper portion
here gives the guideline. 

142
00:10:48,912 --> 00:10:54,285
If the level is adjusted, this guideline
will be parallel to the line of sight 

143
00:10:54,285 --> 00:11:00,497
and thus enable us to make measurements 
on an horizontal plane.  

144
00:11:00,497 --> 00:11:03,902
The measures is done on the staff; 

145
00:11:03,902 --> 00:11:06,792
the graduations of the staff are as following:

146
00:11:06,792 --> 00:11:11,408
you have first the meters,
the decimeters

147
00:11:11,408 --> 00:11:17,343
and then the centimeters that are given here
by the small black and white markers. 

148
00:11:17,343 --> 00:11:24,277
The millimeter will be estimated by eye with 
a precision of plus or minus one millimeter.

149
00:11:24,277 --> 00:11:32,316
In this example here, we can say
that we have one meter, 

150
00:11:32,316 --> 00:11:36,620
we have two decimeters

151
00:11:36,620 --> 00:11:43,063
and we can count the number of 
centimeters starting from here to here

152
00:11:43,063 --> 00:11:47,575
and we have seven centimeters,

153
00:11:47,575 --> 00:11:53,650
and the estimation of millimeters we
give here is about eight millimeters,

154
00:11:53,650 --> 00:12:00,557
so that the height reading
is 1,278 meters.

155
00:12:02,627 --> 00:12:05,740
The measurement principle is as following: 

156
00:12:05,740 --> 00:12:10,127
you have the level that is placed 
here in the middle of the range, 

157
00:12:10,127 --> 00:12:12,923
between point <i>A</i> and point <i>B</i>,

158
00:12:12,923 --> 00:12:16,099
on point <i>A</i> we place a vertical rod

159
00:12:16,099 --> 00:12:18,736
we will make a so-called back reading,

160
00:12:18,736 --> 00:12:24,687
then this rod will move with its
operator to point <i>B</i>

161
00:12:24,687 --> 00:12:27,162
and we will make a front reading; 

162
00:12:27,162 --> 00:12:32,664
here we define a direction of measurement 
and direction of travel, 

163
00:12:32,664 --> 00:12:37,394
that will give an indication 
of the height difference

164
00:12:37,394 --> 00:12:41,100
+ if we ascend, - if we descend 

165
00:12:41,100 --> 00:12:44,394
and height difference is, as
we have already shown, 

166
00:12:44,394 --> 00:12:49,664
the difference between the back reading 
and the front reading. 

167
00:12:49,664 --> 00:12:52,536
Now if we place it in 
the context of a path, 

168
00:12:52,536 --> 00:12:57,241
